   3.9815358087166157`*^9, {3.981568307231123*^9, 3.981568333419224*^9}, {
   3.981568482478155*^9, 3.9815685655845337`*^9}, {3.981568631163067*^9, 
   3.981568633808565*^9}, {3.981568874780283*^9, 3.981568918823801*^9}, {
   3.9815694635665913`*^9, 3.9815694901671715`*^9}, 3.9816139274012947`*^9, {
   3.9816141443063526`*^9, 3.981614144931116*^9}, {3.981614195822729*^9, 
   3.981614223149925*^9}, {3.9816143967987633`*^9, 3.981614402367937*^9}, {
   3.981614749885689*^9, 3.981614758692507*^9}, {3.9816150220877666`*^9, 
   3.981615042681797*^9}, {3.981615949587408*^9, 3.981615986228077*^9}, {
   3.9816263275468636`*^9, 3.98162639556398*^9}, {3.981627710666559*^9, 
   3.9816277331340427`*^9}, {3.981627816871271*^9, 3.981627826775917*^9}, {
   3.9834707788843117`*^9, 3.983470905428894*^9}, {3.98347093597406*^9, 
   3.983470960106243*^9}, {3.9836206455832806`*^9, 3.983620645823761*^9}, {
   3.983620781038639*^9, 3.9836208089740067`*^9}, {3.9876092764290733`*^9, 
   3.9876092902241936`*^9}, {3.9876212028353577`*^9, 3.987621204385351*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[2]:=",ExpressionUUID->"14333812-bb39-034f-830d-93a4e915e12a"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Introduction", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.977222151395748*^9, 3.9772221529422874`*^9}, {
  3.987248847054268*^9, 
  3.987248848804859*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3f73ccbf-8d7a-ce4e-b0c6-\
8a6ef9c10414"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Cosmological observations tightly constrain theoretical descriptions of the \
universe. Measurements of the cosmic microwave background (CMB) fix \
early-universe conditions and global geometry with high precision [",
 ButtonBox["1",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Planck2018"],
 "], while Type Ia supernovae (SNe Ia) probe the late-time expansion history \
through the luminosity distance-redshift relation [",
 ButtonBox["2",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Brout2022"],
 "]. Although each dataset is internally consistent, discrepancies arise when \
parameters inferred from early- and late-time observations are compared. In \
particular, the tension in the Hubble constant [",
 ButtonBox["1",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Planck2018"],
 ", ",
 ButtonBox["3",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Riess2022"],
 "] indicates that the standard cosmological model may be incomplete."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9752634867045307`*^9, 3.975263670517769*^9}, {
   3.975263753238821*^9, 3.9752638119119816`*^9}, {3.975275261507044*^9, 
   3.9752753009800625`*^9}, {3.975275371503805*^9, 3.975275412308817*^9}, {
   3.9772260051831036`*^9, 3.9772260073275833`*^9}, {3.977563568926424*^9, 
   3.9775635787299347`*^9}, {3.977563745422825*^9, 3.977563753290392*^9}, {
   3.977663077686569*^9, 3.977663077702732*^9}, 3.978267791004221*^9, 
   3.979416990747572*^9, 3.979417082043415*^9, 3.9794172097987175`*^9, 
   3.979417451126688*^9, 3.9795649181047153`*^9, 3.979565410690586*^9, 
   3.9798168975516167`*^9, 3.981661129830839*^9, 3.9817973954094257`*^9, {
   3.9817974310656185`*^9, 3.98179746068968*^9}, {3.9872488623985806`*^9, 
   3.9872488750075703`*^9}, 3.987248951789837*^9, {3.9872527866529408`*^9, 
   3.9872527880218067`*^9}, {3.9872529620158463`*^9, 3.987252988612501*^9}, {
   3.987253717922701*^9, 3.9872537755605373`*^9}, {3.9872538221691093`*^9, 
   3.987253835021303*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"635d3ace-93ab-3044-82f7-\
1b911ab70f00"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Historically, such discrepancies have been addressed by extending the \
model. The cosmological constant was introduced to permit a static universe [",
 ButtonBox["4",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Einstein1917"],
 "] and abandoned following the discovery of expansion [",
 ButtonBox["5",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Hubble1929"],
 "]. Galaxy rotation curves motivated the introduction of non-baryonic dark \
matter [",
 ButtonBox["6",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Rubin1980"],
 "], and supernova evidence for accelerated expansion led to the \
reintroduction of the cosmological constant as dark energy [",
 ButtonBox["7",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Riess1998"],
 ", ",
 ButtonBox["8",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Perlmutter1999"],
 "]. While these additions yield a phenomenologically successful framework, \
the dominant components of the cosmic energy budget remain physically \
unexplained [",
 ButtonBox["1",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Planck2018"],
 "]. More recent approaches introduce additional degrees of freedom, \
including time-varying dark energy [",
 ButtonBox["9",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"DiValentino2021"],
 "], further increasing the parametric structure of the model."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9794170870601254`*^9, 3.9794171324433613`*^9}, 
   3.9794174567995777`*^9, {3.9798205083732147`*^9, 3.9798205464979897`*^9}, 
   3.9816611360179825`*^9, 3.9817969126135883`*^9, {3.98179699122155*^9, 
   3.9817969978162727`*^9}, 3.981797404529604*^9, 3.981797438097275*^9, {
   3.98179747148785*^9, 3.9817975008630905`*^9}, {3.9872489611751785`*^9, 
   3.9872489639836826`*^9}, {3.9872573047016697`*^9, 
   3.9872573182944984`*^9}, {3.9872573696808224`*^9, 
   3.9872574027580986`*^9}, {3.987257443959059*^9, 3.9872574570999527`*^9}, {
   3.987257491400921*^9, 3.987257491400921*^9}, {3.987257553272005*^9, 
   3.987257572117859*^9}, {3.9872576043693657`*^9, 3.9872576107677536`*^9}, {
   3.9872576460853176`*^9, 3.987257659231201*^9}, {3.9872581123898125`*^9, 
   3.987258198286625*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9d272470-7916-594d-86b6-\
e713eafac331"],

Cell["\<\
We develop a kinematic framework in which large-scale evolution and local \
gravitational phenomena arise from a common geometric structure, termed the \
Parabolic Metric Evolution (PME). Local metric descriptions specify \
infinitesimal separations, so finite separations between distant events must \
be constructed by integrating along a chosen connection; in a globally \
evolving system, this construction can depend on both the path and the \
evolution of the geometry. The PME framework replaces this path-dependent \
procedure with a bilocal definition that assigns separations directly to \
ordered event pairs while admitting a consistent local limit. Motion on the \
manifold is governed by a single intrinsic kinematic scale, eliminating the \
need for multiple independent cosmological parameters and linking global \
expansion and local dynamics to a common geometric origin. The geometric \
structure of the manifold is illustrated in Fig. 1.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.987248972949503*^9, 3.9872489927670155`*^9}, 
   3.9872514166850796`*^9, {3.98725894333515*^9, 
   3.987258944287506*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3a1596c1-1f4c-d648-b140-\
cd5f70c25329"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This approach differs from relativistic metric gravity in its bilocal \
definition of separation and from modified-gravity models [",
 ButtonBox["10",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"Milgrom1983"],
 ", ",
 ButtonBox["11",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->"McGaugh2016"],
 "] in that the characteristic acceleration scale is not introduced \
phenomenologically but inherited from the global manifold kinematics by the \
local-reduction regime. Cosmological evolution, gravity, and the laws \
governing motion are thereby unified through a single acceleration scale \
determined by the manifold kinematics."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872591573677044`*^9, 3.9872591740548134`*^9}, {
  3.9872592077426777`*^9, 3.987259209822687*^9}, {3.9872593210185127`*^9, 
  3.9872593521322308`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0cff790c-d0b3-3747-9eb3-\
929482a2d555"],

Cell["\<\
The resulting construction defines a minimal kinematic closure: the \
lowest-order geometric structure that consistently relates finite \
separations, global evolution, and local dynamics within a single framework, \
without introducing independent dynamical components. The bilocal definition \
of separation provides a representation of finite intervals compatible with \
global evolution, and the restriction to a single intrinsic acceleration \
scale selects the simplest nontrivial homogeneous dynamics beyond uniform \
motion, yielding a closed and self-consistent description across cosmological \
and local regimes.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.987259364758663*^9, 
  3.9872593695501957`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9c8f799e-48dd-eb44-b6b2-\
76d3ddac7675"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Bilocal Geometry", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.975347253371168*^9, 3.9753472564648876`*^9}, 
   3.987259432116667*^9},ExpressionUUID->"e1cb1589-f369-7c44-badb-\
0f087da4a4fe"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Foundational Structure", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872594519592953`*^9, 
  3.98725947063204*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"477590ba-ea7b-a546-aac9-\
95bf651783e9"],

Cell["The framework is defined by the following postulates:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872594688419113`*^9, 
  3.9872594804921*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"edcdb7b8-d687-b840-8246-a71e9f841150"],

Cell["\<\
Physical separations are defined bilocally between ordered pairs of events.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.987259613928158*^9},ExpressionUUID->"e53a1b7f-316a-164c-a300-\
161065e8fe78"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The manifold evolution is governed by a constant acceleration scale ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       StyleBox["A", "TI"], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$A$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "aa6bce13-2f6d-2f49-9ad3-7341b013e309"],
 "."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872596504904385`*^9, 3.9872596504904385`*^9}, {
  3.987259680617626*^9, 
  3.987259710758692*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"aa4ca5f1-b02d-0b47-9b59-\
dabf62dd9ced"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The manifold is parameterized by an intrinsic evolution coordinate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|
    "boxes" -> FormBox["\[Chi]", TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$\\chi$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "438d84d1-951e-834e-9b47-a1038a9f7a89"],
 "."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872596584127216`*^9, 3.9872596584127216`*^9}, {
  3.987259689749737*^9, 
  3.9872597204593334`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d7b7bba6-3e0a-dc48-bd37-\
771cb7329c36"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Observable time is defined operationally through null exchange, providing \
an invariant ordering of events. The intrinsic evolution parameter is related \
to this observable time by the projection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"\[Chi]", "\[LongEqual]", 
         StyleBox["i", "TI"], 
         StyleBox["t", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$\\chi = i t$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "82de1f9c-f314-9e4c-8244-ab02bf834a27"],
 ", which fixes the real-imaginary decomposition of temporal and spatial \
functionals and serves as a defining structural postulate of the framework."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872596668876953`*^9, 3.9872596668876953`*^9}, {
  3.9872596995529404`*^9, 
  3.9872597393992577`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fdeff846-289b-b14a-aeb7-\
3106903b7cd7"],

Cell["All subsequent results follow from this structure.", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9872597503198757`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"ffb67d92-01e5-9c44-989e-\
37a3729640b8"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Bilocal Spatial Separation", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9872597648717384`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"8f955fd7-b6f0-8f43-8b79-\
e5b3084daa5f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Let ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox[
          StyleBox["p", "TI"], 
          StyleBox["e", "TI"]], "\[LongEqual]", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
             SubsuperscriptBox[
              StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
              StyleBox["e", "TI"], "0"], ",", 
             SubsuperscriptBox[
              StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
              StyleBox["e", "TI"], "1"]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "$p_e=(x_e^0,x_e^1)$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4e38bc9d-46dc-484b-9ea9-63d9b1fc6ed9"],
 " denote an emission event and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox[
          StyleBox["p", "TI"], 
          StyleBox["o", "TI"]], "\[LongEqual]", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
             SubsuperscriptBox[
              StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
              StyleBox["o", "TI"], "0"], ",", 
             SubsuperscriptBox[
              StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
              StyleBox["o", "TI"], "1"]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm], 
     "errors" -> {}, "input" -> "$p_o=(x_o^0,x_o^1)$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c6ebe2f4-b934-934a-8396-b0b835c99265"],
 " an observation event, with the bilocal interval constructed from a \
temporal functional obtained from accumulated evolution between slices and a \
spatial functional defined from separations on the emission and observation \
slices."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9872602473471737`*^9, 
  3.9872602573621407`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6d274375-b7fe-e74b-b0b7-\
9c5a7394be3a"],

